description:
🗣️📚NEW STUDY HOUR📚🗣️

Do you have finals coming up? Do you have papers to write in Spanish? Are you overwhelmed and just want to relax? Worry no more!

CLASHSA’s new study/conversation hour will be a place for you to get study help, work in peace, or just eat Timbits! 🍩🙂‍↕️

This study hour is open to ALL levels, so come on by next Wednesday!

📍Where: SH 688, Room 385
⏰ When: Wednesdays 4:30-5:30

Are you going on exchange to a Spanish-speaking country? Are you overwhelmed and confused by McGill’s lack of information like I was? Never fear, CLASHSA is here! 🌎☀️
 
We are throwing an Exchange Info Night for prospective exchange students! This is a great opportunity to meet other McGill students who are going on exchange and to meet with experts who have already been! 

There will be snacks and drinks, so come on by! 🍿🥤

📍Where: Sherbrooke 688, Room 389 (LLC Lounge)
⏰ When: Friday, November 22nd, 5:30-7:00 pm

Another year, another LLC Collab😎

Join us next Thursday, November 14, for games, drinks, and an opportunity to practice Spanish, German, and Russian in our annual @clashsa.mcgill x @russmcgill x @gsamcgill LLC Social! Free admission provided with one food or drink purchase.

📍 Ye Olde Orchard, 20 Prince Arthur St W
⏰ 7PM

¡Qué asistencia!🎉🎉

Thank you to everyone who came out to celebrate with us for Día de Los Muertos last week💀🇲🇽

Stay tuned for more @clashsa.mcgill events coming soon, ¡hasta la próxima!

Feeling swamped with schoolwork this November season? Looking for an outlet to de-stress? Maybe even practice your Spanish? Or meet fellow Spanish speakers?

Shrek yourself before you wreck yourself! 🧅

Join us this Friday night at Peel Street Cinema for a FREE showing of Shrek in Spanish (English subtitles provided). @clashsa.mcgill x @slasa.mcgill have partnered up to bring you a night that will be anything but medi-ogre!

📍 Where: Peel Street Cinema, 3475 Rue Peel
⏰ When: November 8, 6:30 pm
